l culture across the country; and the considerable continuing power of mystical, supernatural, and 'non-rational' ideas in British social and political life into the nineteenth century. Dr TIM THORNTON teaches at the University of Huddersfield where he is head of department, History, English, Languages and Media.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aProphecyxHistory. 0aProphetszEnglandxHistory. 4aModern History. 7aHISTORY / Modern / General.2bisacsh  aBritish elites.  aBritish social and political life.  aCheshire prophet Nixon.  aMerlin.  aearly modern England.  amystical.  anon-rational ideas.  aprophetic traditions.  asupernatural.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781846155000?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846155000423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846155000/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles